Laryngitis:

• Laryngitis refers to the inflammation of the voice box or the larynx

Symptoms to look for:

• Loss of voice
• Hoarse voice
• Irritation in the throat
• Fever
• Chest congestion
• Cough

Causes:

• Bacterial, viral or fungal infection
• Prolonged cough
• Tuberculosis
• Syphilis
• Allergies
• Bronchitis
• Sinusitis
• Yelling, talking or singing for a long period
• Smoking
• Alcohol

